             depos'd, That he being at Alderman Billers's , he saw the Prisoner take<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="173010140007"></xptr> the Handkerchief out of his Pocket, put it in his Hat, and afterwards threw it on the Ground among the People.</p>
               <p>The Prisoner pleaded, that the Handkerchief was taken up by one South , that desir'd him to go to Sir 
